components.name: FTP File Sensor
components.description: Monitors the FTP server for the presence of vendor_inventory.csv and emits a detection signal when the file becomes available.

connections.purpose: Access FTP server to monitor and download files

components.name: Download Vendor Inventory File
components.description: Downloads vendor_inventory.csv from the FTP server to the local filesystem at /tmp/vendor_inventory.csv.

upstream_policy.description: Executes after successful FTP file detection

components.name: Cleanse Vendor Inventory Data
components.description: Removes null values from critical columns (product_id, quantity, price) in the downloaded vendor inventory CSV.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful download of the vendor file

components.name: Merge Vendor Data with Internal Inventory
components.description: Merges the cleansed vendor inventory data with the internal inventory system on product_id to update stock levels and pricing.

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

destination_path.description: Local filesystem path where the file will be saved

target_columns.description: Columns to cleanse for null values

join_column.description: Column used for joining with internal inventory

sinks: Internal inventory database updated with merged inventory records
intermediate_datasets: cleansed_vendor_data (inmemory or temporary representation after nullvalue removal)
